name: Michelle Tran
blurb: Michelle is a third year computer science major interested in misinformation research, quantum computing, and philanthropic computing. When she's not being a workaholic, Michelle enjoys singing, spending time with her family, and going down Wikipedia/Quora rabbit holes.

blurb: Hi, I'm Michal Bodzianowski! I'm an aspiring creative developer and leader, double majoring in Computer Science and Technology Arts & Media. I love motorsports, esports, and honestly just sports. Fun fact- my name is pronounced ME-how BO-ja-noef-SKEE.

name: Niharika Kunapuli

blurb: I'm Neha, a junior majoring in CS. In my free-time I like reading fantasy and watching Studio Ghibli movies!

name: Anushka Kathait
blurb: Anushka is an undergraduate student majoring in Computer Science and Economics at the University of Colorado Boulder. She is passionate about her fields of study but even more so about service. She currently serves as Blueprint Boulder's Nonprofit Relations and Campus Outreach Lead.

name: Yvonne Liu
blurb: Yvonne is a junior in Computer Science with a minor in Creative Technology and Design. She can be found at the gym or at home cooking some of her favorite dishes.

name: Oceane Andreis
blurb: Océane Andréis is an MS student in the Creative. Technology & Design(social impact track) through the ATLAS institute. She attended the University of Colorado Boulder, receiving a bachelor's degree in computer science with minors in French, leadership studies and TAM in 2020.

name: Huilin Han
blurb: I'm a junior studying Computer Science and Math for the purpose of working on all types of interdisciplinary projects and is always planning when to take the next walk.

blurb: Hello! I'm Jett, a third year undergraduate student working towards a B.S. in computer science with a minor in business. I love working on meaningful & impactful software projects (such as Foster Source's!), watching movies, spending time with friends and family, and learning new things. If you see me around, say hi!
